xwikidoc.title: Import and link maven jar projects to debug
xwikidoc.content:
{{toc/}}
You now have a complete "virtual" XE you can run from Eclipse and where your can edit web files.
We will now see how to link XWiki jar projects (xwiki-core, plugins...) to this XE instance to be able to edit java using all Eclipse tools.
= Import Jar project =
* Start Import wizard
image:import-1.jpg
----
* Select //Maven Projects// * Click image:DebugXEWithEclipse_Resources@buttonnext.jpg
image:import-2.jpg
----
* Select root folder of project you want to import * Click image:DebugXEWithEclipse_Resources@buttonfinish.jpg
image:import-3.jpg
== Link Jar project to the web project ==
Go to project ##Properties -> Deployment Assembly# and add the project.
